<a href="javascript:card_browser(149)">Orc Assassin</a> x3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Now the point of this deck is pretty obvious on the fellowship side: Cancel as many skirmishes as Possible, unless you feel safe. Arwen&#39;s great in this deck. Also, get 3 home 3 allies set up. The shadow side is the fun part though:<br>
<br>
Each minion listed costs -1-2. Moria Scout will often come out for free. But the key to this deck, is to save up minions for site 4, and don&#39;t go after a hobbit. Try to overwhelm a man or an elf. It&#39;s likely at site 4, that a stealth or Intuition will be in their hand. The biggest problem is Big Fellowships. If you can get out Swarms at the beginning, it would be great. The Forger is great in this deck, because you could use the extra twilight and exhaust him, or let him take an archery wound. This is the advantage this deck has over swarm decks. Many of the 1-cost minions have 2 vitality. So if you save up for 1 big bombardment on every other site or something, they&#39;ll keep losing companions. Remember: Keep Frodo alive. FIND THE HALFLINGS! KILL THE OTHERS! But with less companions, the other player will die... Maybe a bit later, but they still will. If you wish, Such A Little Things would help in this deck. Thanks for reading it. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25165"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25165" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
